  "root_text": {
    "snp1.8:0.1": "Sutta Nipāta 1.8 ",
    "snp1.8:0.2": "Mettasutta ",
    "snp1.8:1.1": "“Karaṇīyamatthakusalena, ",
    "snp1.8:1.2": "Yanta santaṁ padaṁ abhisamecca; ",
    "snp1.8:1.3": "Sakko ujū ca suhujū ca, ",
    "snp1.8:1.4": "Sūvaco cassa mudu anatimānī. ",
    "snp1.8:2.1": "Santussako ca subharo ca, ",
    "snp1.8:2.2": "Appakicco ca sallahukavutti; ",
    "snp1.8:2.3": "Santindriyo ca nipako ca, ",
    "snp1.8:2.4": "Appagabbho kulesvananugiddho. ",
    "snp1.8:3.1": "Na ca khuddamācare kiñci, ",
    "snp1.8:3.2": "Yena viññū pare upavadeyyuṁ; ",
    "snp1.8:3.3": "Sukhino va khemino hontu, ",
    "snp1.8:3.4": "Sabbasattā bhavantu sukhitattā. ",
    "snp1.8:4.1": "Ye keci pāṇabhūtatthi, ",
    "snp1.8:4.2": "Tasā vā thāvarā vanavasesā; ",
    "snp1.8:4.3": "Dīghā vā ye va mahantā, ",
    "snp1.8:4.4": "Majjhimā rassakā aṇukathūlā. ",
    "snp1.8:5.1": "Diṭṭhā vā ye va adiṭṭhā, ",
    "snp1.8:5.2": "Ye va dūre vasanti avidūre; ",
    "snp1.8:5.3": "Bhūtā va sambhavesī va, ",
    "snp1.8:5.4": "Sabbasattā bhavantu sukhitattā. ",
    "snp1.8:6.1": "Na paro paraṁ nikubbetha, ",
    "snp1.8:6.2": "Nātimaññetha katthaci na kañci; ",
    "snp1.8:6.3": "Byārosanā paṭighasañña, ",
    "snp1.8:6.4": "Nāññamaññassa dukkhamiccheyya. ",
    "snp1.8:7.1": "Mātā yathā niyaṁ puttam ",
    "snp1.8:7.2": "Āyusā ekaputtamanurakkhe; ",
    "snp1.8:7.3": "Evampi sabbabhūtesu, ",
    "snp1.8:7.4": "Mānasaṁ bhāvaye aparimāṇaṁ. ",
    "snp1.8:8.1": "Mettañca sabbalokasmi, ",
    "snp1.8:8.2": "Mānasaṁ bhāvaye aparimāṇaṁ; ",
    "snp1.8:8.3": "Uddhaṁ adho ca tiriyañca, ",
    "snp1.8:8.4": "Asambādhaṁ averamasapattaṁ. ",
    "snp1.8:9.1": "Tiṭṭhaṁ caraṁ nisinno va, ",
    "snp1.8:9.2": "Sayāno yāvatāssa vitamiddho; ",
    "snp1.8:9.3": "Etaṁ satiṁ adhiṭṭheyya, ",
    "snp1.8:9.4": "Brahmametaṁ vihāramidhamāhu. ",
    "snp1.8:10.1": "Diṭṭhiñca anupaggamma, ",
    "snp1.8:10.2": "Sīlavā dassanena sampanno; ",
    "snp1.8:10.3": "Kāmesu vinaya gedhaṁ, ",
    "snp1.8:10.4": "Na hi jātuggabbhaseyya punaretī”ti. ",
    "snp1.8:10.5": "Mettasuttaṁ aṭṭhamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "snp1.8:0.1": "Anthology of Discourses 1.8 ",
    "snp1.8:0.2": "The Discourse on Love ",
    "snp1.8:1.1": "Those who are skilled in the meaning of scripture ",
    "snp1.8:1.2": "should practice as follows <j>to realize the state of peace. ",
    "snp1.8:1.3": "Let them be capable and upright, very upright, ",
    "snp1.8:1.4": "easy to speak to, gentle and humble; ",
    "snp1.8:2.1": "content and unburdensome, ",
    "snp1.8:2.2": "unbusied, living lightly, ",
    "snp1.8:2.3": "alert, with senses calmed, ",
    "snp1.8:2.4": "courteous, not fawning on families. ",
    "snp1.8:3.1": "Let them not do the slightest thing ",
    "snp1.8:3.2": "that others who are wise would blame. ",
    "snp1.8:3.3": "May they be happy and safe! ",
    "snp1.8:3.4": "May all beings be happy! ",
    "snp1.8:4.1": "Whatever living creatures there are ",
    "snp1.8:4.2": "with not a one left out—",
    "snp1.8:4.3": "frail or firm, long or large, ",
    "snp1.8:4.4": "medium, small, tiny or round, ",
    "snp1.8:5.1": "seen or unseen, ",
    "snp1.8:5.2": "living far or near, ",
    "snp1.8:5.3": "those who have been born <j>and those about to be born—",
    "snp1.8:5.4": "may all beings be happy! ",
    "snp1.8:6.1": "Let none deceive another, ",
    "snp1.8:6.2": "nor look down on anyone anywhere. ",
    "snp1.8:6.3": "Though provoked or aggrieved, ",
    "snp1.8:6.4": "let them not wish pain on each other. ",
    "snp1.8:7.1": "Even as a mother would protect with her life ",
    "snp1.8:7.2": "her child, her only child, ",
    "snp1.8:7.3": "so too for all creatures ",
    "snp1.8:7.4": "unfold a boundless heart. ",
    "snp1.8:8.1": "With love for the whole world, ",
    "snp1.8:8.2": "unfold a boundless heart: ",
    "snp1.8:8.3": "above, below, all round, ",
    "snp1.8:8.4": "unconstricted, without enmity or foe. ",
    "snp1.8:9.1": "When standing, walking, sitting, ",
    "snp1.8:9.2": "or lying down while yet unweary, ",
    "snp1.8:9.3": "keep this ever in mind; ",
    "snp1.8:9.4": "for this, they say, is a divine meditation <j>in this life. ",
    "snp1.8:10.1": "Avoiding harmful views, ",
    "snp1.8:10.2": "virtuous, accomplished in insight, ",
    "snp1.8:10.3": "with desire for sensual pleasures dispelled, ",
    "snp1.8:10.4": "they never return to a womb again. "
  },
